text: Kulesa is a settlement in Kenya's Coast Province. A small village in the Tana River county in the Tana Dela District in Salama Location, Maziwa sub- location. It has a population of about 400 families; approximately 3200 people. The residents are all Christian by faith. The dominant denomination is the Lutheran Church- KELC with a 97% of the population. Category:Populated places in Coast Province
title: Kulesa
